reviewText:
b-beatifuel end ;~;

I have both of naruto and i must say , i like this game's alot , even thoe i don't play so much those kind of game's

There is only some small negative's what we can normaly ignore or talk about

i want thx to creator's for making this beatifuel game for us , can't wait for continue ;v;

Excellent title; the main campaign (Ninja World Tournament) is nice, but nothing special; the Ninja adventures (the 2 Uchiha & Akatsuki origins) are great, and with a perfect dubbing SYNC.

About gameplay:
+++: Ultimate Team Jitsu: some of them, are really amazing;
+++: now all ultimate jitsu have sound effects, not like in Naruto UNS 3 (in that game, they have a decent impact only if you kill the enemy using them);
+++: great idea to give a basic awekening and a true awekening to all characters. I really suggest to CyberConnect 2 to keep this conception in UNS 4;
+++: there are a lot of survival tournament, and I want even more of them in Naruto Shippuden UNS 4 because they are the best way to continue playing even after finishing the campaign. About this, PLEASE DO A SERIOUS AKATSUKI SURVIVAL MODE (with all the 10 members to fight: Deidara, Sasori, Hidan, Kakuzu, Itachi, Konan, Pain, Kisame, Obito & Madara could be a good sequence to follow);
---: all throw jitsu that crush the enemy to the ground have awful (totally lacking in impact) sound effects (they were 10 times better in UNS 3);
---: I don't like the idea of choosing 1 style of combat; it reduces gameplay variety (because you can use only something, and not the whole arsenal of the selected character).

My final rank: 9/10.
